AIM
To encrypt text using one-time pad key stream, and then find an alternate key that produces another plaintext.
alphabet = "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz"

def otp_encrypt(text, key):
    text = text.replace(" ", "")
    nums = [alphabet.index(c) for c in text]
    cipher_nums = [(nums[i] + key[i]) % 26 for i in range(len(nums))]
    return ''.join(alphabet[n] for n in cipher_nums)

def otp_find_key(cipher, plaintext):
    cipher_nums = [alphabet.index(c) for c in cipher]
    plain_nums = [alphabet.index(c) for c in plaintext]
    key = [(cipher_nums[i] - plain_nums[i]) % 26 for i in range(len(cipher_nums))]
    return key

plaintext = "sendmoremoney"
key = [9,0,1,7,23,15,21,14,11,11,2,8,9]

cipher = otp_encrypt(plaintext, key)
print("Cipher:", cipher)

alt_plain = "cashnotneeded"
new_key = otp_find_key(cipher, alt_plain)
print("New key stream:", new_key)
RESULT
OTP encryption is performed, and an alternative key is generated that decrypts the same ciphertext into another plaintext.
